headline: Outrage in Italy over online spread of degrading images of women
description: Hundreds of women – including Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni, Democratic Party leader Elly Schlein, and several artists – have fallen victim to obscene photomontages and doctored photos.

headline: Strong earthquake strikes eastern Afghanistan, killing over 600 people
description: The magnitude 6.0 earthquake struck the area near the Pakistani border at night on Sunday, September 1, killing at least 800 people. At least five aftershocks, including one measured at magnitude 5.2, followed it.

description: Ouahiba Bouzyane, 52, arrived from Morocco in 2002 after marrying a French man. Following a divorce and a new relationship, she is now a single mother of five in Paris.

headline: Lorde, New Zealand electropop sensation: 'With 'Virgin,' I wanted to document my femininity'
description: Twelve years ago, while still a teenager, the singer rose to fame with her hit song 'Royals.' Quickly endorsed by some of the biggest names in music, the 28-year-old's unique voice and bold songwriting were a departure from music industry standards. She has just released her raw fourth album, 'Virgin,' and will perform at the Zénith in Paris on November 10.

headline: Video: Why are young African women manufacturing Russian drones?
description: The Alabuga Special Economic Zone, in Tatarstan, Russia, has been producing drones since the start of the war in Ukraine. There, young African women have found themselves working on production lines, lured by a misleading vocational training program.
byline: Marceau Bretonnier,  Sinead McCausland and  Thomas Eydoux
